<div class="dcf-wrapper">
  <div class="header">
    <div class="header-content">
      <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
      <h1>O'Reilly Automotive (ORLY)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of O'Reilly Automotive — using real actuals, disclosed assumptions mathematically derived from market risk factors, and one final number.</p>
      <p class="date">Updated March 24, 2026</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
    <div class="verdict-card">
      <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
      <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
      <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${currentPrice.toFixed(2)} ({marginOfSafety}%)</div>
      <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
        {verdictText}
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
    <div class="stats-row">
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">${(rev2024 / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Most Recent Revenue</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">${(fcf2024 / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">${eps2024.toFixed(2)}</div>
        <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">{opMargin2024.toFixed(1)}%</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Operating Margin</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
    <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
    <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model — projecting the cash flows of O'Reilly Automotive forward, then discounting them back to today's value.</p>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">1</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
        <p>ORLY generated <strong>${(fcf2024 / 1000).toFixed(2)} billion</strong> in free cash flow recently. This forms our baseline Phase 1 year-0 cash flow.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">2</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
        <p>We grow FCF at <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}% per year</strong> for 5 years. This rate is derived mathematically from the firm's historical free cash flow compounding, capped to a sustainable ceiling.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">3</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
        <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}% forever</strong>. This is tied dynamically to the long-term risk-free rate.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">4</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
        <p>All future cash flows are discounted at <strong>{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</strong> — mathematically derived using the Capital Asset Pricing Model (CAPM). It uses the 10-Year Treasury rate ({ (treasuryRate * 100).toFixed(2) }%) and ORLY's beta ({beta}).</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">5</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
        <p>Enterprise Value + Net Cash (${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(2)}B) = Equity Value. Divide by shares outstanding ({sharesOutstanding.toFixed(2)}M) for the per-share intrinsic value.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
    <h2>Assumptions and Rationale</h2>

    <div class="assumption-grid">
      <div class="assumption-card">
        <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Phase 1)</div>
        <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
        <div class="rationale">
          Derived from historical FCF compounding. We use this rate for the high-growth Phase 1 to accurately model near-term momentum without fabricating rosy assumptions.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="assumption-card">
        <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
        <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
        <div class="rationale">
          10Y Treasury Rate is {(treasuryRate * 100).toFixed(2)}%. Given ORLY's beta of {beta} and an equity risk premium of {(erp * 100).toFixed(1)}%, CAPM dictates this discount rate to properly reflect investment risk.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="assumption-card">
        <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
        <div class="value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
        <div class="rationale">
          Anchored safely below the long-term risk-free rate. A perpetuity growth rate cannot sustainably exceed nominal macroeconomic growth.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ FCF PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
    <h2>Projected Free Cash Flows</h2>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
            <th>FCF ($M)</th>
            <th>PV Factor</th>
            <th>Present Value ($M)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Base</td>
            <td>${fcf2024.toLocaleString(undefined, {maximumFractionDigits:0})}</td>
            <td>—</td>
            <td>—</td>
          </tr>
          {projectedFCF.map(p => (
            <tr>
              <td>Year {p.year}</td>
              <td>${p.fcf.toLocaleString(undefined, {maximumFractionDigits:0})}</td>
              <td>{p.pvFactor.toFixed(4)}</td>
              <td>${p.pvFCF.toLocaleString(undefined, {maximumFractionDigits:0})}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
          <tr class="row-total">
            <td colspan="3">Sum of Phase 1 PV</td>
            <td class="highlight-cell">${pvPhase1.toLocaleString(undefined, {maximumFractionDigits:0})}</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ TERMINAL VALUE ═══ -->
    <h3>Terminal Value</h3>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
            <th>Value ($M)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Year 6 FCF (Year 5 × {(1 + growthRateTerminal).toFixed(3)})</td>
            <td>${Math.round(fcfYear6).toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Terminal Value</td>
            <td>${terminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="row-total">
            <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
            <td class="highlight-cell">${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ FINAL CALCULATION ═══ -->
    <h3>Final Valuation</h3>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
            <th>Value ($M)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>PV of Phase 1 Cash Flows</td>
            <td>${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
            <td>${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>= Enterprise Value</td>
            <td>${enterpriseValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>+ Net Cash (Cash − Debt)</td>
            <td>${Math.round(netCash).toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>= Equity Value</td>
            <td>${Math.round(equityValue).toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>÷ Shares Outstanding</td>
            <td>{sharesOutstanding.toFixed(2)}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="row-total">
            <td>Intrinsic Value Per Share</td>
            <td class="highlight-cell">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ HISTORICAL CHARTS ═══ -->
    <h2>Financial Track Record</h2>

    <h3>Revenue ($M)</h3>
    <div class="bar-chart">
      {revenueHistory.map(r => (
        <div class="bar-row">
          <div class="bar-label">{r.year}</div>
          <div class="bar-track">
            <div class="bar-fill revenue" style={`width: ${Math.max(10, (r.value / rev2024) * 100)}%`}>
              ${r.value.toLocaleString(undefined, {maximumFractionDigits:0})}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <h3>Free Cash Flow ($M)</h3>
    <div class="bar-chart">
      {fcfHistoryChart.map(r => (
        <div class="bar-row">
          <div class="bar-label">{r.year}</div>
          <div class="bar-track">
            <div class="bar-fill fcf" style={`width: ${Math.max(10, (r.value / fcf2024) * 100)}%`}>
              ${r.value.toLocaleString(undefined, {maximumFractionDigits:0})}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <h3>Earnings Per Share (Diluted)</h3>
    <div class="bar-chart">
      {epsHistoryChart.map(r => (
        <div class="bar-row">
          <div class="bar-label">{r.year}</div>
          <div class="bar-track">
            <div class="bar-fill eps" style={`width: ${Math.max(10, (r.value / eps2024) * 100)}%`}>
              ${r.value.toFixed(2)}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ SENSITIVITY ANALYSIS ═══ -->
    <h2>Sensitivity Analysis</h2>
    <p>How intrinsic value changes with variations in discount rate and growth rate.</p>

    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table class="sensitivity-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th style="text-align:left">Discount Rate ↓ / Growth →</th>
            {sensitivityGrowth.map(g => (
              <th class={Math.abs(g - growthRatePhase1) < 0.001 ? 'current' : ''}>{(g * 100).toFixed(1)}%</th>
            ))}
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {sensitivityTable.map(row => (
            <tr>
              <td>{(row.dr * 100).toFixed(1)}%</td>
              {row.values.map((v, i) => (
                <td class={Math.abs(row.dr - discountRate) < 0.001 && Math.abs(sensitivityGrowth[i] - growthRatePhase1) < 0.001 ? 'current' : ''}>
                  ${v}
                </td>
              ))}
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ RISKS ═══ -->
    <h2>What This Model Doesn't Capture</h2>
    <h3>Upside risks (our number could be too low)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Accelerated Buybacks:</strong> ORLY repurchases stock aggressively. Fewer shares outstanding in the future inherently increases per-share value.</li>
      <li><strong>Market Share Gains:</strong> Expansion in commercial sales could drive revenue beyond historical trajectories.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Downside risks (our number could be too high)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>EV Transition:</strong> Electric vehicles have fewer moving parts, potentially reducing the long-term total addressable market for replacement auto parts.</li>
      <li><strong>Debt Costs:</strong> Higher-for-longer interest rates could pressure free cash flow as long-term debt matures and rolls over.</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- ═══ FAQ ═══ -->
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="faq">
      <details>
        <summary>Why use DCF instead of a P/E multiple?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">Multiples indicate what the market is currently willing to pay. A DCF forces mathematical rigor based strictly on cash-generating capacity and market risk rates.</div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Why use CAPM for the discount rate?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">The Capital Asset Pricing Model ensures our required rate of return reflects the actual risk profile (beta) of the stock against a baseline safe yield (10Y Treasury).</div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Is this a buy recommendation?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">No. This is purely an analytical framework based on mathematical derivatives of current financial data. Always conduct your own due diligence.</div>
      </details>
    </div>

